    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  We show how a common microwave oven, a coat-hanger and a coffee cup can be used to decontaminate N-95 respirators in 30 seconds. Tulane virus in artificial saliva was reduced by &gt;3 log and\n                  <jats:italic>Geobacillus stearothermophilus</jats:italic>\n                  spores were reduced by &gt;6 log. Respirators maintained filtration and fitting after 10 cycles.\n                </jats:p>",
